Package: till
Version: 1.1.0-1
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: bash (>= 5), coreutils, util-linux, mmdebstrap, sudo
Recommends: bash-completion
Maintainer: You <0foo.dev>
Description: Tiny per-project Debian chroot environment manager (mmdebstrap + chroot)
 This tool bootstraps a minimal Debian root filesystem per project using
 mmdebstrap and provides convenient commands to enter and destroy it
 using real chroot isolation. By default, it uses unshare-based mount
 namespaces for automatic cleanup when you exit.
 .
 Commands:
  - 'till build'   : create or update the Debian rootfs
  - 'till enter'   : enter the environment (bind-mounts PWD by default)
  - 'till destroy' : unmount and delete the environment
